ible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000465-GPOS-00209","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-002884","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"7357","uuid":"1d76ead5-6b21-44b1-a423-1882ee57b89b","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64DC96407EC220E69C73C6DA99FE2FBE25EA9EE3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the chcon command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274096","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274096","title":"SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274096","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172","rule_id_src":"SV-274096r1120276_rule","rule_id":"SV-274096","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002160","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /var/log/faillock.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/var/log/faillock\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /var/log/faillock -p wa -k logins\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/var/log/faillock\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep /var/log/faillock\n-w /var/log/faillock -p wa -k logins\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit records specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002884","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"4096","uuid":"0a9535f4-c954-4d7e-acc8-d6fe40cc39eb","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2970989EE58E8F9BC452B35D059A2997A74DD932\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /var/log/faillock.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274097","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274097","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274097","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-274097r1120279_rule","rule_id":"SV-274097","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002165","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /var/log/lastlog.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/var/log/lastlog\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /var/log/lastlog -p wa -k logins\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/var/log/lastlog\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep /var/log/lastlog\n-w /var/log/lastlog -p wa -k logins\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit records specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-002884","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1658","uuid":"88f6f43a-3bf8-4ddf-89da-fdbd271f65ae","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 611D0701F5FE97B992F4271C81E59CD84959B6FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /var/log/lastlog.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274098","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274098","title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274098","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","rule_id_src":"SV-274098r1120282_rule","rule_id":"SV-274098","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002175","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the init command.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit system generates an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful uses of the \"init\" command by adding or updating the following rule in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\" file:\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/init -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-init\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured to audit the execution of the \"init\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep init\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/init -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-init\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Misuse of the init command may cause availability issues for the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"2157","uuid":"4f097fbf-efd2-40ed-b3d2-bba2a555b8e6","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA8B5D0AD365FF81A1A65136FB0140B1C8B4881C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the init command.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274099","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274099","title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274099","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","rule_id_src":"SV-274099r1120285_rule","rule_id":"SV-274099","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002180","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the reboot command.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit system generates an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful uses of the \"reboot\" command by adding or updating the following rule in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\" file:\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/reboot -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-reboot\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured to audit the execution of the \"reboot\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep reboot\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/reboot -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-reboot\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Misuse of the reboot command may cause availability issues for the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9024","uuid":"e1d17971-3c59-4a55-8402-20024944ff5c","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-274100","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274100","title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274100","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","rule_id_src":"SV-274100r1120288_rule","rule_id":"SV-274100","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002185","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the shutdown command.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit system generates an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful uses of the \"shutdown\" command by adding or updating the following rule in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\" file:\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/shutdown -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-shutdown\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured to audit the execution of the \"shutdown\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep shutdown\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/shutdown -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-shutdown\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Misuse of the shutdown command may cause availability issues for the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"2925","uuid":"e3e277ca-2cc5-427d-95d7-88565d19d97f","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 305AC52DF4573406C737F7A802650FE8A9BFB55B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the shutdown command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274101","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274101","title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274101","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","rule_id_src":"SV-274101r1120291_rule","rule_id":"SV-274101","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002190","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools must have a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools to have a mode of \"0755\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0755 [audit_tool]\n\nReplace \"[audit_tool]\" with each audit tool that has a more permissive mode than \"0755\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools have a mode of \"0755\" or less with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%a %n\" /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/rsyslogd /sbin/augenrules\n755 /sbin/auditctl\n755 /sbin/aureport\n755 /sbin/ausearch\n750 /sbin/autrace\n755 /sbin/auditd\n755 /sbin/rsyslogd\n755 /sbin/augenrules\n\nIf any of the audit tool files have a mode more permissive than \"0755\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protecting audit information also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit information.\n\nOperating systems providing tools to interface with audit information will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys to make access decisions regarding the access to audit tools.\n\nAudit tools include, but are not limited to, vendor-provided and open source audit tools needed to successfully view and manipulate audit information system activity and records. Audit tools include custom queries and report generators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001493"],"reference_identifier":"6678","uuid":"e335fcb1-8397-4be4-8dd2-3ab2e7fcd999","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1AB9D4371300D6AD9B56C8F77EE9BE79A62C767C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools must have a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274102","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274102","title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274102","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","rule_id_src":"SV-274102r1120294_rule","rule_id":"SV-274102","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002195","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools must be owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools to be owned by \"root\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root [audit_tool]\n\nReplace \"[audit_tool]\" with each audit tool not owned by \"root\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%U %n\" /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/rsyslogd /sbin/augenrules\nroot /sbin/auditctl\nroot /sbin/aureport\nroot /sbin/ausearch\nroot /sbin/autrace\nroot /sbin/auditd\nroot /sbin/rsyslogd\nroot /sbin/augenrules\n\nIf any audit tools do not have an owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protecting audit information also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit information.\n\nOperating systems providing tools to interface with audit information will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys to make access decisions regarding the access to audit tools.\n\nAudit tools include, but are not limited to, vendor-provided and open source audit tools needed to successfully view and manipulate audit information system activity and records. Audit tools include custom queries and report generators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001493"],"reference_identifier":"8780","uuid":"944c1f58-fbde-457b-aea9-377755f65427","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 65516B6EF5CF80E5A176F55574534507C0CDCB92\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools must be owned by root.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274103","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274103","title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274103","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000256-GPOS-00097","rule_id_src":"SV-274103r1120297_rule","rule_id":"SV-274103","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002200","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools must be group-owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools to be group-owned by \"root\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [audit_tool]\n\nReplace \"[audit_tool]\" with each audit tool not group-owned by \"root\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit tools are group owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/rsyslogd /sbin/augenrules\nroot /sbin/auditctl\nroot /sbin/aureport\nroot /sbin/ausearch\nroot /sbin/autrace\nroot /sbin/auditd\nroot /sbin/rsyslogd\nroot /sbin/augenrules\n\nIf any audit tools do not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protecting audit information also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit information.\n\nOperating systems providing tools to interface with audit information will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys to make access decisions regarding the access to audit tools.\n\nAudit tools include, but are not limited to, vendor-provided and open source audit tools needed to successfully view and manipulate audit information system activity and records. Audit tools include custom queries and report generators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001493"],"reference_identifier":"3631","uuid":"35be3a6d-1315-4535-b9eb-a08a13afeca5","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-274104","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274104","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274104","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-274104r1120300_rule","rule_id":"SV-274104","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002205","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/passwd.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/passwd\".\n\nEnable the auditd daemon so that it can start at boot time:\n\n$ sudo systemctl enable auditd\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n-w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity\n\nThen, restart the auditd service for the changes to take effect:\n\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/passwd\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | egrep '(/etc/passwd)' \n-w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Once an attacker establishes access to a system, the attacker often attempts to create a persistent method of reestablishing access. One way to accomplish this is for the attacker to create an account. Auditing account creation actions provides logging that can be used for forensic purposes.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221, SRG-OS-000274-GPOS-00104, SRG-OS-000275-GPOS-00105, SRG-OS-000276-GPOS-00106, SRG-OS-000277-GPOS-00107","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"7913","uuid":"63f71891-9e29-4982-bd43-7b1ed68bd39e","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8EDB892A534BBFAC27E000C7524D80199C386300\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/passwd.' is not present or not in use on this the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274105","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274105","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274105","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-274105r1120661_rule","rule_id":"SV-274105","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002210","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all successful/unsuccessful uses of the chage command.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit service generates an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful uses of the \"chage\" command by adding or updating the following rule in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\" file:\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/chage -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-chage\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that an audit event is generated for any successful/unsuccessful use of the \"chage\" command by performing the following command to check the file system rules in \"/etc/audit/audit.rules\":\n\n$ sudo grep -w chage /etc/audit/audit.rules\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/chage -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-chage\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Reconstruction of harmful events or forensic analysis is not possible if audit records do not contain enough information.\n\nAt a minimum, the organization must audit the full-text recording of privileged commands. The organization must maintain audit trails in sufficient detail to reconstruct events to determine the cause and impact of compromise.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-002884","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1879","uuid":"7fef088c-de9d-4ab3-b71d-ed59d42d9275","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DAD1CBD03E8D02FF18A4B4E4388488038912C128\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all successful/unsuccessful uses of the chage command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274107","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274107","title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274107","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","rule_id_src":"SV-274107r1120309_rule","rule_id":"SV-274107","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002220","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must off-load audit records onto a different system in the event the audit storage volume is full.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to off-load audit logs in the event the audit storage volume becomes full.\n\nAdd or update the following line (depending on configuration \"disk_full_action\" can be set to \"SYSLOG\" or \"SINGLE\" depending on configuration) in \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" file:\n\ndisk_full_action = SYSLOG","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 takes the appropriate action when the audit storage volume is full using the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep disk_full_action /etc/audit/auditd.conf\ndisk_full_action = SYSLOG\n\nIf the value of the \"disk_full_action\" option is not \"SYSLOG\", \"SINGLE\", or \"HALT\", or the line is commented out, ask the system administrator to indicate how the system takes appropriate action when an audit storage volume is full. If there is no evidence of appropriate action, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.\n\nOff-loading is a common process in information systems with limited audit storage capacity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"5674","uuid":"bf13ec17-5db8-4e88-a2e0-93e0e72f5906","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 32C3AFE90C0C93EC8E02D80E5E801EB62A98EDDB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must off-load audit records onto a different system in the event the audit storage volume is full.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274108","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274108","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274108","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-274108r1120312_rule","rule_id":"SV-274108","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002225","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs must be group-owned by root or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that audit logs are group-owned by \"root\" or a restricted logging group.\n\nChange the group of the directory of \"/var/log/audit\" to be owned by a correct group.\n\nIdentify the group that is configured to own audit log:\n\n$ sudo grep -P '^[ ]*log_group[ ]+=.*$' /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nChange the ownership to that group:\n\n$ sudo chgrp ${GROUP} /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs are group-owned by \"root\" or a restricted logging group. \n\nFirst determine if a group other than \"root\" has been assigned to the audit logs with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep log_group /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_group = root\n\nThen determine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nThen using the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log is group-owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /var/log/audit/audit.log\nroot /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit log is not group-owned by \"root\" or the configured alternative logging group, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nAudit information includes all information (e.g., audit records, audit settings, audit reports) needed to successfully audit operating system activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"3490","uuid":"0dc24aea-a242-47fb-9a81-2545672a4897","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 957661312446DF086C7206CF9998EC6EF3A904C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs must be group-owned by root or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274109","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274109","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274109","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-274109r1120315_rule","rule_id":"SV-274109","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002230","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit log directory must be owned by root to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit logs directory is protected from unauthorized read access by setting the correct owner as \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs directory is owned by \"root\". \n\nFirst determine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nThen using the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log directory is owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo ls -ld /var/log/audit\ndrwx------ 2 root root 23 Jun 11 11:56 /var/log/audit\n\nIf the audit log directory is not owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nAudit information includes all information (e.g., audit records, audit settings, audit reports) needed to successfully audit operating system activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"4637","uuid":"eb6e7101-2a23-4aea-8532-4d6bf2b96ba5","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 35ED7F2B45DB27C09D6CD119F2314C5F529D2CEE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit log directory must be owned by root to prevent unauthorized read access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274110","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274110","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274110","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-274110r1120318_rule","rule_id":"SV-274110","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002235","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs file must have mode \"0600\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized access to the audit log.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit logs have a mode of \"0600\".\n\nReplace \"[audit_log_file]\" to the correct audit log path, by default this location is \"/var/log/audit/audit.log\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 0600 /var/log/audit/[audit_log_file]\n\nCheck the group that owns the system audit logs:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_group /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nIf the log_group is not defined or it is set to root, configure the permissions as follows:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0640 $log_file\n$ sudo chmod 0440 $log_file.*\n\nOtherwise, configure the permissions as follows:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0600 $log_file\n$ sudo chmod 0400 $log_file.*","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs have a mode of \"0600\". \n\nFirst determine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nThen using the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log files as a mode of \"0640\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /var/log/audit/ -type f -exec stat -c '%a %n' {} \\;\n600 /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit logs have a mode more permissive than \"0600\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nAudit information includes all information (e.g., audit records, audit settings, audit reports) needed to successfully audit operating system activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"7552","uuid":"6f4c1966-b746-4f09-a3d7-30d0965482c4","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A5717F970C6DFAA302A27AD966455FF137612111\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs file must have mode \"0600\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized access to the audit log.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274111","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274111","title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274111","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","rule_id_src":"SV-274111r1120321_rule","rule_id":"SV-274111","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002240","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must allow only the information system security manager (ISSM) (or individuals or roles appointed by the ISSM) to select which auditable events are to be audited.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that files in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/\" and the \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" file have a mode of \"0640\" or less permissive with the following commands:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0640 /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\n$ sudo chmod 0640 /etc/audit/rules.d/[customrulesfile].rules\n$ sudo chmod 0640 /etc/audit/auditd.conf","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that files in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/\" and the \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" file have a mode of \"0640\" or less permissive by using the following commands:\n\n$ sudo find /etc/audit/rules.d/ /etc/audit/audit.rules /etc/audit/auditd.conf -type f -exec stat -c \"%a %n\" {} \\;\n600 /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\n640 /etc/audit/audit.rules\n640 /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nIf the files in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/\" directory or the \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" file have a mode more permissive than \"0640\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the capability to restrict which roles and individuals can select which events are audited, unauthorized personnel may be able to prevent the auditing of critical events. Misconfigured audits may degrade the system's performance by overwhelming the audit log. Misconfigured audits may also make it more difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000171"],"reference_identifier":"7413","uuid":"7492c0b2-ba98-4dbf-909d-f3bc2f7b0167","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2AE538A0543201D0D00F8AFB2A4976A1F04E9D12\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must allow only the information system security manager (ISSM) (or individuals or roles appointed by the ISSM) to select which auditable events are to be audited.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274112","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274112","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274112","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-274112r1120324_rule","rule_id":"SV-274112","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002245","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the sudo command.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit system generates an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful use of the \"sudo\" command by adding or updating the following rule in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\" file:\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/sudo -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k priv_cmd\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured to audit the execution of the \"sudo\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep '/usr/bin/sudo\\b'\n-a always,exit -S all -F path=/usr/bin/sudo -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=-1 -F key=priv_cmd\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit records specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"1670","uuid":"8b53dc34-38c3-4ea9-aa48-2c7a349d1db5","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EBF67FC6A94FF5F25047BACB7F236D159C7D3DE2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must audit all uses of the sudo command.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274113","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274113","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274113","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-274113r1120327_rule","rule_id":"SV-274113","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002250","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/passwd.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/passwd\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/passwd\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | egrep '(/etc/passwd)' \n-w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In addition to auditing new user and group accounts, these watches will alert the system administrator(s) (SAs) to any modifications. Any unexpected users, groups, or modifications should be investigated for legitimacy.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221, SRG-OS-000274-GPOS-00104, SRG-OS-000275-GPOS-00105, SRG-OS-000276-GPOS-00106, SRG-OS-000277-GPOS-00107","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"4435","uuid":"d67df245-5595-4783-a76d-ee838ef75c6b","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-274114","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274114","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274114","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-274114r1120330_rule","rule_id":"SV-274114","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002255","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/shadow.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/shadow\".\n\nAdd or update the following file system rule to \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-w /etc/shadow -p wa -k identity\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command: \n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 generates audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect \"/etc/shadow with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | egrep '(/etc/shadow)' \n-w /etc/shadow -p wa -k identity\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In addition to auditing new user and group accounts, these watches will alert the system administrator(s) (SAs) to any modifications. Any unexpected users, groups, or modifications should be investigated for legitimacy.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000304-GPOS-00121, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221, SRG-OS-000275-GPOS-00105","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000015","CCI-002884","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"3421","uuid":"bd0c26b1-5ee2-4573-a8a0-9a424225c7c9","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3E3C89E7A3EEE28779090E961C2823EC9F0C6C29\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must generate audit records for all account creations, modifications, disabling, and termination events that affect /etc/shadow.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274115","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274115","title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274115","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","rule_id_src":"SV-274115r1120333_rule","rule_id":"SV-274115","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002260","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must produce audit records containing information to establish the identity of any individual or process associated with the event.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the audit system resolves audit information before writing to disk.\n\nEdit the /etc/audit/auditd.conf file and add or update the \"log_format\" option:\n\nlog_format = ENRICHED\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that the audit system resolves audit information before writing to disk, with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep log_format /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_format = ENRICHED\n\nIf the \"log_format\" option is not \"ENRICHED\", or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without information that establishes the identity of the subjects (i.e., users or processes acting on behalf of users) associated with the events, security personnel cannot determine responsibility for the potentially harmful event.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001487"],"reference_identifier":"6267","uuid":"16709f82-37a3-4f74-bf73-ef9a83a776cc","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E340C8BD4944B422A422A843AD277B2F3733788D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must produce audit records containing information to establish the identity of any individual or process associated with the event.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274116","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274116","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274116","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-274116r1120336_rule","rule_id":"SV-274116","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002265","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs must be group-owned by root or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 to change the group of the directory of \"/var/log/audit\" to be owned by a correct group.\n\nIdentify the group that is configured to own audit log:\n\n$ sudo grep -P '^[ ]*log_group[ ]+=.*$' /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nChange the ownership to that group:\n\n$ sudo chgrp ${GROUP} /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that the audit logs are group-owned by \"root\" or a restricted logging group. \n\nFirst determine if a group other than \"root\" has been assigned to the audit logs with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep log_group /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nThen determine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nThen using the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log is group-owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /var/log/audit/audit.log\nroot /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit log is not group-owned by \"root\" or the configured alternative logging group, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify Amazon Linux 2023 or platform. Additionally, Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"1980","uuid":"1deec925-9a35-471e-b550-e056e3950307","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CAF93B50D54502035D10C953BCCEBB4D69873967\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs must be group-owned by root or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274117","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274117","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274117","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-274117r1120339_rule","rule_id":"SV-274117","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002270","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must ensure the audit log directory be owned by root to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 audit logs to be protected from unauthorized read access by setting the correct owner as \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that the audit logs directory is owned by \"root\". \n\nFirst determine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nThen using the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log directory is owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\nsudo stat -c '%U %n' /var/log/audit\nroot /var/log/audit\n\nIf the audit log directory is not owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify Amazon Linux 2023 or platform. Additionally, Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"6652","uuid":"e2784b2c-9743-4d53-9832-fe7249c0497c","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 043681A0D5CF0168D0B47CD1D27A3D3E7F041982\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must ensure the audit log directory be owned by root to prevent unauthorized read access.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274119","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274119","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274119","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274119r1120345_rule","rule_id":"SV-274119","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002280","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must be group-owned by root or a system account.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib and /usr/lib64) to be protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory not group-owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories are group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -group root -type d -exec stat -c \"%n %G\" '{}' \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library directory is returned and is not group-owned by a required system account, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs which execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals shall be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"9613","uuid":"0f2d1872-afae-4096-9364-428fdc8fadd1","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77D7E937A10F56A13150A50650638ECCADF4EE63\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must be group-owned by root or a system account.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274120","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274120","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274120","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274120r1120348_rule","rule_id":"SV-274120","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002285","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must have mode \"755\" or less permissive.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib and /usr/lib64) to be protected from unauthorized access. \n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory with a mode more permissive than \"755\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 755 [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories have mode \"755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -perm /022 -type d -exec ls -l {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library file is found to be group-writable or world-writable, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs which execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals shall be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"4445","uuid":"eff4920d-862d-4472-94ed-c7d0e8fd3d61","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B1EFB23E4895086D277A9D1EC61BC84D5E5B0A6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must have mode \"755\" or less permissive.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274121","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274121","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274121","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274121r1155161_rule","rule_id":"SV-274121","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002290","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library files must have mode \"755\" or less permissive.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" have mode 0755 or less permissive with the following command.\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' -perm /022 -exec chmod go-w {} +","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" have mode 0755 or less permissive.\n\nCheck that the systemwide shared library files have mode 0755 or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' -perm /022 -exec stat -c \"%n %a\" {} +\n\nIf any output is returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals will be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"8553","uuid":"5310d00a-ae95-4ba6-9a9b-782ee6f7d1e8","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DA83194EB313B6DB7B24617DBD540EEA7D999F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 library files must have mode \"755\" or less permissive.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274122","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274122","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274122","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274122r1155164_rule","rule_id":"SV-274122","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002295","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library files must be owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" to be owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' ! -user root -exec chown root {} +","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" are owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' ! -user root -exec stat -c \"%n %U\" {} +\n\nIf any output is returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals shall be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"4542","uuid":"acfc4848-81f1-47de-b90a-24260f0f3e0f","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB09914F0B2CC9ABC8792505461BA01667A7A51F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 library files must be owned by root.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274123","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274123","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274123","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274123r1155167_rule","rule_id":"SV-274123","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002300","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library files must be group-owned by root or a system account.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" to be group owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' ! -group root -exec chown :root {} +","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library files contained in the directories \"/lib\", \"/lib64\", \"/usr/lib\", and \"/usr/lib64\" are group owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -type f -name '*.so*' ! -group root -exec stat -c \"%n %G\" {} +\n\nIf any output is returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs which execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals shall be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"8131","uuid":"f8cd328f-5d8a-4841-9765-5a137ff538a7","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 143305B951BF82528DEDC4028D5AFB5E02D35A65\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Amazon Linux 2023 library files must be group-owned by root or a system account.' is not present or not in use on this the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274124","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274124","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274124","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-274124r1120360_rule","rule_id":"SV-274124","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002305","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must be owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories within (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib and /usr/lib64) to be protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory not owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chown root [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 systemwide shared library directories are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -user root -type d -exec stat -c \"%n %U\" '{}' \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library directory is not owned by root, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If Amazon Linux 2023 were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to operating systems with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs which execute with escalated privileges. Only qualified and authorized individuals shall be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"8670","uuid":"99d91122-f706-48a8-8705-51349021bb18","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5033F4D42CA6B7118465748E2D50C4159B49BADE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 library directories must be owned by root.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274125","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274125","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274125","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-274125r1120363_rule","rule_id":"SV-274125","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002315","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must ensure the /var/log directory have mode \"0755\" or less permissive.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the \"/var/log\" directory has a mode of \"0755\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0755 /var/log","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify Amazon Linux 2023 is configured so that the \"/var/log\" directory has a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c '%a %n' /var/log\n755 /var/log\n\nIf \"/var/log\" does not have a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Amazon_Linux_2023_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify Amazon Linux 2023 or platform. Additionally, Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"4807","uuid":"44fdb875-9e79-443d-91ea-1005103f2f71","stig_uuid":"2f88c1a6-c04a-4834-ace0-b775886d4b01","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AmazonLinux2023_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8E59809137DD79CEB71474A4ABAAF926E7907CA2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Amazon Linux 2023 must ensure the /var/log directory have mode \"0755\" or less permissive.' matches the expected value on the Amazon Linux 2023 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-274126","group_tree":[{"id":"V-274126","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-274126","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-274126r1120366_rule","rule_id":"SV-274126","rule_version":"AZLX-23-002320","rule_title":"Amazon Linux 2023 must ensure the /var/log directory be owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure Amazon Linux 2023 so that the directory \"/var/log\" is owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /var/log","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify 